# AxiomOS Development Mode

Follow `docs/MASTER_ROADMAP.md` as the single source of truth.

## Current Sprint Focus
- **Active:** 5.A.5 ADT Generator Engine (in progress)
- **Next:** 5.A.6 ADT Certification
- **Blocked until 5.A.15:** Phase 5B Identity Platform business modules

## Every Sprint Must Deliver
Design → Code → Tests → Browser Demo → APIs → Doc Updates → Review → Next

## Do NOT
- Create documentation-only sprints or new 30-page spec documents
- Re-debate locked architecture (see ARCHITECTURE_FREEZE.md)
- Skip simulation/approval for ADT generators (Rule 0)
- Start Identity/business modules before ADT certification (5.A.6)

## Do
- Ship working code with tests and browser demo every 2–4 days
- Update module README/CHANGELOG only (no new doc frameworks)
- Run `composer quality:gate` before closing a sprint
- Reference ADRs only when core architecture changes

## Existing Code
`modules/Organization` already has Org/Company/Branch/Department — align in 5.B.4–5.B.7, do not duplicate.

## Human Architect Role
User reviews, approves ADRs, solves blockers. AI implements per roadmap.
